{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a7b52bf8-ccd7-4a8e-a084-d6f95be7f17a","content":"Set these environment variables before launching your app:\n\n```bash\n# Enable crash dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\n\n# Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\n\n# Output path (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/var/dumps/coredump.%d.%t.dmp\n```\n\nMake sure the target directory exists and is writable:\n\n```bash\nsudo mkdir -p /var/dumps\nsudo chmod 1777 /var/dumps\n```\n\n**Verify the configuration:**\n\n```bash\n# Confirm the vars are set in your process\ncat /proc/<PID>/environ | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep DOTNET_Dbg\n\n# Test with a deliberate crash (dev/staging only)\nkill -s SIGABRT <PID>\n\n# Check that a dump was written\nls -lh /var/dumps/\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `DOTNET_` prefix replaced the older `COMPlus_` prefix starting in .NET 7. Both still work, but `DOTNET_` is preferred for .NET 10.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e4311693-a765-48b3-bd51-0a8d054c8566","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about configuring automatic crash dump collection for a .NET 10 CoreCLR application running on Linux. This is a knowledge question about .NET runtime configuration, not a code change task. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"CB01:2C00FF:1FA6634:22E903D:6A0529BF"},"id":"4017bb80-28ed-4523-83dd-9296626bab00","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:47:52.073Z","parentId":"3e12623e-f41e-4186-9992-c0ee1ce49d31"}
